                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The First Committee held two meetings on January 29; for the records, see United
                    Nations documents A/C.1/SR.433 and 434. At the afternoon session, the Lebanese
                    Representative (Malik) introduced two amendments to the United States draft
                    resolution covering the points already agreed upon in United States–United
                    Kingdom discussions over the past several days. The first amendment called for
                        <pb facs="0162" n="146" xml:id="pg_146"/> changing Paragraph 2 by replacing
                    the words “rejected all” with “not accepted”; the second amendment proposed
                    adding at the end of paragraph 8 the words “it being understood that the
                    Committee is authorized to defer its report if the Good Offices Committee,
                    referred to in the following paragraph, reports satisfactory progress in its
                    efforts”. (United Nations document A/C.1/656)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
